      <hedline>
        <hl1>Fuel-Efficiency Caveat</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bruce Atlas letter says he would support mass marketing of hybrid gas-electric cars and improvements of fuel-cell technology to reduce US dependence on oil and production of airborne pollutants, 'just so long as the use of my big sedan and small, supercharged sports car is not affected' (Sept 17 letter)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Like a Sept. 17 letter writer, I would support mass marketing of hybrid gas-electric cars and improvements of fuel-cell technology to reduce this country's dependence on oil and production of airborne pollutants, just as long as the use of my big sedan and small, supercharged sports car is not affected.</p>
        <p>BRUCE ATLAS  Whitestone, Queens, Sept. 17, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
